# Step 1: Ignore environment files so secrets and machine-specific configs are not committed.
# Why: .env files often contain API keys and private configuration that must not be pushed.
# Result: Git will ignore common dotenv files and variants by default.

# Common dotenv files
.env
.env.*
*.env
*.env.*
.envrc

# Allow example/template env files to be committed for configuration reference
!.env.example
!*.env.example 